    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-09-17T04:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-09-17T04:25:00-05:00" n="633"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d633">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1203: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-17T12:00:00+02:35"
                            >September 17, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>96. The message in your 56, September 12, 6 p.m., and the statement in circular
                    September 13th<note n="74" xml:id="d633fn74">Not printed; it contained summary
                        of the Secretary’s statement to the press, of September 12, 1935, <ref
                            target="#pg_746">p. 746</ref>.</note> have created a most excellent
                    impression and are gratefully appreciated.</p>
                <p>My informant states that the inquiry in my 92<note n="75" xml:id="d633fn75"
                        >September 10, 3 p.m., <ref target="#pg_744">p. 744</ref>.</note> was based
                    on the assumption that League action would fail and was not intended to request
                    American diplomatic intervention except as a last resort to avert war. The
                    Emperor seems prepared to go the utmost limit of concession compatible with
                    national honor and dignity.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
